After ESA holidays are coming up. They are going to last for n days.

During the holidays, Rohan wants to try all of these activities exactly once with his friends:

1.) go to swimmig pool

2.) watch a movie

3.) play COD

Rohan knows that, on the i -th day, exactly

Ai friends will join him for swimmig,

Bi friends will join him for a movie

Ci friends will join him for COD.

Rohan also knows that he can't try more than one activity in a single day.

Thus, he asks you to help him choose three distinct days p,q,r in such a way that the total number of friends to join him for the activities (Ap+Bq+Cr ) is maximized.

Input Format

The first line of each testcase contains a single integer n — the duration of the holidays in days.

The second line contains n integers A1,A2,…,An — the number of friends that will join Rohan for swimming on the i -th day.

The third line contains n integers B1,B2,…,Bn — the number of friends that will join Rohan for a movie on the i -th day.

The fourth line contains n integers C1,C2,…,Cn — the number of friends that will join Rohan for COD on the i -th day.

Constraints

1 <= n <= 10^5

1 <= Ai , Bi , Ci <= 10^8

Output Format

the maximum total number of friends that can join Rohan for the activities on three distinct days.

Sample Input 0

3
1 10 1
10 1 1
1 1 10
Sample Output 0

30
Explanation 0

Rohan can choose day 2 for swimming, day 1 for a movie and day 3 for COD. This way,

A2=10 friends will join him for swimming,

B1=10 friends will join him for a movie and

C3=10 friends will join him for COD.

The total number of friends is 30 .